    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-24T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-24T04:00:00-05:00" n="872"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d872">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/860</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-24T10:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1917, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 25, 12.24 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1224. I have ascertained that a Finnish contingent has come to Stockholm and was
                    received privately by Weden, president of the Rigsdag, in one of the committees
                    of Parliament. The Finns asked for the recognition of the independence of
                    Finland and for the military assistance of Sweden in order to expel the Russians
                    from Finland in the event of the Russians refusing to recognize the independence
                    of Finland. As military assistance might involve losses for Sweden no agreement
                    was reached and the negotiations were dropped.</p>
                <pb facs="0829" n="739" xml:id="pg_739"/>
                <p>Three Finnish delegations are leaving Stockholm for Berlin, London, and
                    Washington. The first is composed of <persName>Hjelt</persName> and
                        <persName>Erich</persName>, the second of <persName>Holsti</persName> and
                        <persName>Kihlman</persName>, and the-third of <persName corresp="#p_RJN1"
                        >Reuter</persName> and <persName>Soskimo</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MIN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
